act:
187742 THE PATENTS (AMENDMENT) ACT, 2005
NO. 15 OF 2005 [ 4th April, 2005]
An Act further to amend the Patents Act, 1970.
BE it enacted by Parliament in the Fifty- sixth Year of the Republic of India as follows:-
1581431 1 Short title and commencement.-
834480 1This Act may be called the Patents (Amendment) Act, 2005.
1460852 2Sub- clause (ii) of clause (a), and clause (b), of section 37, sections 41, 42, 47, 59 to 63 (both inclusive) and 74 shall come into force on such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint; and the remaining provisions of this Act shall be deemed to have come into force on the 1st day of January, 2005.
